    "date": "2021-12-17T18:03:16Z",
    "text": "Vaccine Access Improvement Act of 2021\n\nThis bill adds vaccines recommended by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) for routine administration to children or in pregnant women to the list of taxable vaccines for purposes of the vaccine excise tax. The CDC must notify the Department of the Treasury and specified congressional committees of the designation of such vaccines as taxable vaccines."
